        <div class="section movable text" id="50cc9e3f061b44eba2c18cd3c09a849f" data-type="text" data-js-class="TextSection" data-dj-class="TextSection" data-layout-position="1">
    <div class="head">
        <div class="grip"></div>
        
        
    </div>
    <div class="notify"></div>
    <div class="body"  data-button-class="all">
        <p>
Congratulations on your decision to learn how to quit smoking! Now that you have made this important decision, you may be interested in learning tips and advice to help you through what may prove to be a difficult process. There are a variety of methods that are used to help smokers kick the habit. 
</p><p>
According to the America Heart Association and a survey performed by the National Center for Health Statistics, there are an estimated 46 million smokers in the United States. This number represents approximately 23 percent of the male population and 18 percent of the female population of the country. <ref>http://www.americanheart.org/presenter.jhtml?identifier=4559</ref>The <a href="/centers-for-disease-control" title="Centers for Disease Control">CDC or Center for Disease Control</a> and Prevention reports that Kentucky has the highest population of smokers in the U.S. and the U.S. Virgin Islands has the lowest population of smokers. <ref>http://www.webmd.com/smoking-cessation/news/20070927/whre-states-rank-in-adult-smokers</ref>
</p>
    </div>
</div>

     
